<h2>The weather in January 2021</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
The temperature in January was below normal in western Europe and above normal in eastern Europe (figure 8). In Spain and Portugal the coldest night of the month was exceptionally below average, whereas the warmest daytime of the month was exceptionally above average (figure 10). The timeseries of nighttime and daytime temperatures for Valencia (figure 11) indeed show low nighttime temperatures in the first half of the month and high daytime temperatures towards the end of the month.
<br><br>
